Authors: Marshall J.
Title: A Validation of Lead CheckÂ® Swabs for the Detection of Lead on Objects at a Crime Scene
Author Keywords: The Sodium Rhodizonate Test is currently used to indicate possible bullet holes through the detection of all forms of lead (vapour; particles etc.) on objects. Lead Check swabs were developed to be a quick; safe; and easy way to detect lead on painted surfaces. Such swabs could be useful as a presumptive test for lead at crime scenes. The effectiveness of the two testing techniques on different media was compared after test firing bullets into different media (plywood; cotton clothing; denim; drywall and automobile body metal) at a distance of 1 yard. The specificity for lead of the swabs was comparedagainst different metals (copper; zinc; barium; etc.). The swabs performed equally well on all the test media used. It was also determined that although the swabs by themselves were not specific for lead; an additional treatment of the surface with a 5% solution of hydrochloric acid (HCl) allowed the swabs to be used to distinguish between lead and elements similar to lead (barium; thallium and cadmium). The conclusion was reached that the Lead Check swabs can be a useful presumptive test for lead in forensic identification and crime scene work.
Index Keywords: Gunshot Residues; Lead Check Swabs; Sodium Rhodizonate Test

Authors: Jacobson J., Swanepoel J.M., Wong K.S.
Title: Evaluation of PlumbtesmoÂ® and CuprotesmoÂ® Test Paper for Sensitivity to Lead and Copper Residues
Author Keywords: The Sodium Rhodizonate Test and the Dithiooxamide (DTO) Test are currently used to indicate possible bullet holes and bullet impact strike marks through the detection of lead and copper residue. Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo also detect lead and copper even though they were not originally designed for forensic use. This study shows that Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo can however be useful in forensic applications (detection of lead and copper residue) on various surfaces that range from cotton fabric; denim; leather; sheetrock; plywood; smooth concrete; rough concrete and asphalt to vehicle bodies. All these surfaces are commonly associated with crime scenes. Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo were tested in conjunction with Sodium Rhodizonate and DTO on similar surfaces and under similar conditions. Results show that Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo detected lead and copper as effectively as Sodium Rhodizonate and DTO. The Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo tests also showed that the test papers (strips) are highly specific in reaction to lead and copper residues respectively and did not demonstrate any cross-reactivity with other metals that were tested. Plumbtesmo and Cuprotesmo test strips offer advantages in ease of use; being small; lightweight; compact; non-toxic and provide an almost immediate and identifiable reaction to lead and copper residues.
Index Keywords: Bullet Impact; Bullet Impact Residues; Cuprotesmo; Dithiooxamide (DTO) Test; Gunshot Residues; Lead Check Swabs; Plumbtesmo; Sodium Rhodizonate Test
